title: 1788–89 United States presidential election
added: The Constitution, in [[Article Two of the United States Constitution#Section 1, Clause 2|Article II, Section 1]], provided that the state legislatures should decide the manner in which their Electors were chosen.  Different state legislatures chose different methods:<ref>{{cite web|title=The Electoral Count for the Presidential Election of 1789 |work=The Papers of George Washington |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130914141726/http://gwpapers.virginia.edu/documents/presidential/electoral.html|archivedate=September 14, 2013|url=http://gwpapers.virginia.edu/documents/presidential/electoral.html |accessdate=May 4, 2005}}</ref>
